{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"All direct and transitive dependencies are extracted from the manifest and included in the vulnerability check.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"The failure boundary is module handoff: manifest parsing + transitive-resolution + scan input assembly. A one-function Unit test can miss dropped transitive deps at wiring boundaries (MOCK-MISS). No behavior text requires real OS/network/subprocess, so System is rejected; extraction can be validated with in-process fixtures and a fake vuln client capture (REAL-INFRA rejection). No AI/model dependency, so Agentic/Workflow are rejected.","test_description":"Run the dependency-extraction pipeline end-to-end in-process on fixture manifests/lockfiles containing nested transitives, then assert the exact dependency set passed into the vulnerability-check stage includes all expected direct and transitive packages.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.72,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The vulnerability database query returns results that match the exact version ranges in the manifest, not just the package name.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This behavior targets query construction/response filtering across scanner and vuln-DB client modules. A Unit test of only semver matching is too narrow; the realistic bug is often at the client/filter boundary (MOCK-MISS). Real network is not required to catch this specific failure; deterministic stubbed API responses with overlapping package names and different ranges are sufficient, so System is rejected by behavior text (REAL-INFRA rejection). No AI dependency.","test_description":"Wire scanner + vuln-client adapter against a stub HTTP server/client fixture that returns multiple CVEs for same package with differing affected ranges; verify final matched CVEs correspond only to manifest version constraints.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.18,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The severity sorting places Critical above High above Medium above Low, with CVEs of the same severity sorted by CVSS score.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is pure local ordering logic on provided records with no I/O or module-boundary dependency. The described failure is algorithmic comparator behavior, so Unit is sufficient. Higher levels are rejected because behavior text does not require infra interaction, model output, or orchestration.","test_description":"Call the sort/comparator function with mixed severities and tied severities with different CVSS values, and assert exact order: Critical>High>Medium>Low, then descending CVSS within each severity.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.93,"Integration":0.06,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"The manifest modification changes only the affected dependency's version, leaving all other entries unchanged.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Real failure commonly appears across parse->modify->serialize/file-write modules, where unrelated entries can be reformatted or mutated during roundtrip (MOCK-MISS). This needs multi-module wiring, not just a one-function update assertion. No real OS/network/subprocess semantics are required beyond local in-process/file fixture behavior, so System is rejected.","test_description":"Execute manifest update flow on fixture manifests containing many dependencies/metadata; assert only target dependency version changes and all other entries (keys/values and expected formatting-preservation rules) remain unchanged.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.24,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"The auto-generated pull request is created on the real repository with the correct single-dependency diff.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior explicitly requires creation on a real repository and validating the resulting diff in real Git/remote API flow. Mocking can hide auth, branch, commit, and diff integration failures (MOCK-HIDE, REAL-INFRA). Agentic/Workflow are rejected because no AI decision quality is involved.","test_description":"Against a real test repository and real VCS hosting API, run PR creation flow, then verify an actual PR exists and its diff contains exactly one dependency version change and no unrelated file changes.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.0,"Integration":0.05,"System":0.94,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":6,"description":"A major version bump is correctly identified as a breaking change based on semver comparison.","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is deterministic semver classification logic at a single function/object boundary with no I/O. The failure is local algorithmic correctness; integration or system infrastructure is unnecessary. No AI dependency.","test_description":"Test semver comparison function with representative cases (major/minor/patch/pre-release) and assert only major bump paths are marked breaking.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.95,"Integration":0.04,"System":0.01,"Agentic":0.0,"Workflow":0.0}},{"behavior_id":7,"description":"When a breaking change is detected, PR creation is skipped and a review flag is surfaced in the scanner output.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration across modules: semver decision output must gate PR module invocation and propagate a review flag into scanner output. A pure Unit test of semver logic would miss handoff/state propagation bugs (MOCK-MISS). No real network/OS/subprocess is required to verify skip behavior; a fake PR client and output sink catch it, so System is rejected. No AI/model dependency and no multi-agentic sequence.","test_description":"Run scanner orchestration in-process with a breaking-update fixture, injecting a spy/fake PR client; assert PR client is not called and scanner output includes the expected review-required flag/details.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.17,"Integration":0.78,"System":0.04,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.0}}]}
